<h2>Introduction</h2>
	<p> This is Michelle Bae, a graduate from The University of Hong Kong with a major in accounting and finance. Born in Korea, I moved to Singapore when I was two and spent eight years of my childhood. There, I attended a Korean kindergarten and started my primary school years in the Canadian International School. I came back to Korea and completed primary school in a Korean local school, and I graduated from middle and high school in Korea International School. And now it has been four years since I moved to Hong Kong, while I studied accounting and finance in The University of Hong Kong. Having lived in Singapore, Korea, and Hong Kong, areas with the most competitive and rigorous education systems, I have never stopped my passion for learning, and now I am about to start a new adventure in learning computer programming. I hope I take the lessons learnt throughout my life to heart, always be open to learn, and have continuous eagerness like that of a high school student studying for college exams to be a positive impact on our community and to better our world. I hope the coding skills that I will develop soon in particular will help my ideas come to life much more easily and I wish I can build a collaborative community myself to grow together and make a better future. </p>

